<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

When you wrote your message on the wrapped paper, each letter got written in a different position. When you unwrapped it, the message looked jumbled because the letters were no longer in order.

But when you wrapped it again on a stick of the same thickness (radius), the letters came back in the right order.

This is how the **Scytale cipher** works — it's an ancient way of coding and decoding messages. It's the same idea that computers use today in **encryption** — hiding information and unlocking it with a matching "key."

